<task id="041" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-08 `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` schema-aware — object-typed fields render as labeled key-value blocks (fixes R5 Entities bug)</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <outcome-note>
      Closed 2026-06-09 by sub-agent. Task 040's extension-point handoff worked
      cleanly — flipped `classifySchemaField()` object branch (one-line change),
      added `else if (classification === 'object')` branch at dispatch site,
      authored `parseObject()` helper + `prettyName()` humanizer + new
      `<SchemaAwareObjectRenderer />` component + `renderObjectValue()`
      recursive helper. Nested array properties REUSE task 040's
      `<SchemaAwareArrayRenderer />` directly (verified by test asserting
      `data-display-hint="schema-array"` on nested lists) — no duplicate
      implementation per Q5 architectural decision. Depth guard bails to
      compact JSON.stringify with TODO marker for depth-≥-2 (Phase B
      constraint). 23 tests pass (12 task 040 baseline + 11 new for task 041).
      Widget grew 1385 → 1775 LOC; test file grew 494 → 846 LOC. BFF publish-
      size delta = 0 MB (frontend-only). ADR-012 / ADR-021 / ADR-029 / ADR-030
      compliance verified via self-audit + new DOM-scan dark-mode test on
      object renderer subtree. Did NOT refactor task 040's top-level array
      dispatch into a generic helper (acceptance criterion #1 said "if needed";
      kept stable to minimize regression surface — the reuse happens at the
      component level via direct `<SchemaAwareArrayRenderer />` mounting from
      `renderObjectValue`). Live D365 UI walkthrough deferred to main session
      at Phase B exit gate. Evidence note:
      `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-041-widget-object-rendering-evidence.md`.
    </outcome-note>
    <estimated-effort>3-4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>040</dependencies>
    <blocks>042, 048</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, react, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Frontend code implementation in `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx`; extends shared widget; fixes R5 Entities rendering bug (Gap C); 6+ steps; FULL rigor mandatory per CLAUDE.md §8.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B-G3</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Same file as task 040 (`StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx`) — SEQUENTIAL with 040 (depends on 040 to land the accumulate-parse-dispatch plumbing first). Cannot run truly in parallel with 040.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` (already updated in task 040 with
    accumulate-parse-dispatch plumbing + array dispatch) with OBJECT-typed field
    rendering: when the action's `outputSchema` declares a field as `{ type: "object" }`
    with nested properties (e.g., `entities: { organizations: string[], persons:
    string[] }` from `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`), render it as labeled
    key-value blocks — one labeled section per nested property, with the nested value
    formatted appropriately (nested arrays → inner bulleted list reusing task 040's
    code path; nested strings → plain text). This structurally fixes the R5 SC-18 bug
    where `entities` rendered as a raw JSON object literal (Gap C in R5 lessons-learned).

    Task 040 must land FIRST — it establishes accumulate-parse-dispatch plumbing + array
    case. This task adds the object case to the existing dispatch switch. The two tasks
    share the same file; cannot run in parallel.

    The widget continues to: gracefully fall back when `outputSchema` is absent; handle
    malformed JSON; respect Fluent UI v9 theming + ADR-021 dark mode; keep
    streaming-in-progress indicator until `streaming_complete`. The object dispatch must
    REUSE the task-040 array rendering code path for nested array-typed properties (do
    NOT duplicate the implementation).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer with deep
    familiarity with the SpaarkeAi widget framework and the `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`
    after task 040's update. Comfortable extending the dispatch switch and composing
    recursive rendering for nested types.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` renders object-typed fields as Fluent v9 labeled
    key-value blocks. The R5 SC-18 entities rendering bug is structurally fixed
    (`entities` no longer renders as raw JSON object literal). Object dispatch reuses
    task 040's array code path for nested arrays. Backward compatibility preserved. All
    unit tests pass (array + object + fallback + malformed JSON cases). Dark-mode
    compliance verified per ADR-021.
  </goal>

