    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 labeled key-value block" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-theming.md">
        Use `<Label>` from `@fluentui/react-components` for the field key + tokens-styled
        container for the value. Typical layout: vertical stack of `<div>` rows with
        `display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: tokens.spacingVerticalS`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Recursive renderValue pattern" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx">
        Extract a `renderValue(value: unknown, schema?: JsonSchema)` helper that
        dispatches: `array of string` → bulleted list (task 040 path); `object with
        properties` → labeled key-value blocks (this task); `string` → plain text.
        Recurse for nested array-typed properties within an object.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="R5 lessons-learned Gap C — entities bug" location="projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/lessons-learned.md">
        `entities: { organizations: string[], persons: string[] }` rendered as raw JSON
        object literal. Fixing this is the second half of the schema-aware widget
        upgrade (task 040 = arrays; task 041 = objects).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 SC-18 walkthrough surfaced that `entities: { organizations: string[], persons:
      string[] }` rendered as a raw JSON object literal in the workspace tab — the
      widget had no way to dispatch on `type: object`. Task 040 shipped the
      accumulate-parse-dispatch plumbing plus array dispatch. THIS task extends the
      dispatch switch with the object case: each nested property becomes a labeled
      block (`Organizations: ...`; `Persons: ...`), and for nested array values, REUSE
      task 040's bulleted list rendering. The net effect: a clean grouped UI for
      multi-field structured output.

      Depth limit: nested object-of-object (e.g., `entities.organizations[0].address`)
      is out of scope for Phase B and falls back to compact JSON. Future phases may
      extend recursion depth.
    </background>
