      <item>Task 033 supplied the data foundation (action outputSchema includes the entities object).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Frontend code implementation in shared widget; fixes R5 Gap C
                 (entities bug); 6+ steps; ADR-012 + ADR-021 binding
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS: all 12 steps below INCLUDING Step 9.5 quality gates + ui-tests
                         (Step 9.7)
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 041 status 🔲; dep (040) complete. Verify task 040's
      array dispatch is working in current branch (git log or test run).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Read the post-task-040
      `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` IN FULL — understand where the dispatch switch
      lives. Read R5 lessons-learned Gap C entities sub-evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Refactor: Extract `renderValue` Helper">
      Before adding the object case, refactor task 040's inline array rendering into a
      `renderValue(value: unknown, schema?: JsonSchema)` helper. This keeps the dispatch
      switch clean as new cases are added. Verify unit tests still pass after refactor.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Object Dispatch">
      Extend `renderValue`: when schema is `{ type: "object", properties: { ... } }`,
      iterate properties; for each property, render `<div className={labeledBlock}>
      <Label>{prettyName(propKey)}</Label> {renderValue(value[propKey],
      properties[propKey])} </div>`. Use Fluent v9 `Label` + tokens-styled vertical
      stack. RECURSE into `renderValue` for nested values — array properties
      automatically reuse task 040's bulleted list.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement Depth Guard">
      Track recursion depth (or detect nested object-of-object). If depth ≥ 2 and inner
      type is object: fall back to compact JSON.stringify with a TODO marker in widget
      code. Document this as a known Phase B constraint.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Extend `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.test.tsx`:
      (a) object-typed field renders as labeled key-value blocks (e.g., `entities` ->
          `Organizations: [bullets]; Persons: [bullets]`);
      (b) nested array within object reuses bulleted list rendering;
      (c) depth-≥-2 object-of-object falls back to compact JSON with TODO marker;
      (d) all task-040 tests still pass after the refactor (regression).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build + Verify BFF Publish-Size">
      Run `npm run build` for the widget library. Confirm BFF publish-size delta is 0 MB.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below. Record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` against the widget + test changes. Run `adr-check`; verify
      ADR-012 (Fluent v9), ADR-021 (dark-mode tokens), ADR-029 (BFF delta = 0), ADR-030
      (PaneEventBus unchanged). Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="9.7" name="UI Tests (per ui-tests section)">
      Run UI tests defined below via ui-test skill. Verify object dispatch + dark mode.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update TASK-INDEX.md: 041 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

